==Cookery==

The most celebrated of the breams in cookery are the [[gilt-head bream]] and the [[common dentex]].&lt;ref&gt;[[Alan Davidson (food writer)|Davidson, A.]] ''Mediterranean Seafood'', Penguin, 1972. {{ISBN|0-14-046174-4}}, pp. 86–108.&lt;/ref&gt;

